    <note>Cheng(1) Yu(6) [15699] See documentation for sons, Fan [3102], Xiang [3103] and Chong [3099]. He died in Huangzhou, Huangpo county when children still young. Both Fan and Xiang received initial appointments through the influence of their elder lineage cousin, Cheng(1) Lin [118]. Yu(6) may have held a minor office, probably in Huangpo. He buried his father, Xizhen [15698], in Henan and therefore moved the family to Luoyang. I date the move with Xizhen.</note>
